{
    "name": "Smoke Haunt",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Said to form from the spirits of lost wanderers slain by exposure and despair, smoke haunts hunger for life, warmth, and a home they\u2019re cursed to never find again."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<img src=\"images\\ThreeFiveSymbol.gif\" style=\"margin: 3px 3px 0px 3px\"/><i>The smell of wood smoke bears the taint of burning flesh. A branch in the campfire sputters and hisses. From within the fire\u2019s embers a smoldering skull glares out, its eyes wells of cold darkness. Tendrils of smoke dance around and through it like tongues or writhing snakes.</i>",
